data.title: 28 fun facts for February, 29 (+3 bonus) - Historical events, discover what happened on this day.
data.meta_description: February 29th, known as Leap Day, boasts a variety of fun facts, including the birth of Levi Strauss and the founding of San Francisco. From the first same-sex marriage representation in a TV show to Google's "AlphaGo" defeating a Go world champion, these unique events are celebrated only once every four years.
